{
  "slug": "rigid-heddle-lace-weave-scarf",
  "title": "Rigid heddle lace weave scarf",
  "subtitle": "Open-work fabric using a pickup stick to lift alternate warp threads",
  "excerpt": "A 20 cm x 150 cm scarf woven on a rigid heddle loom. The lace effect comes from a pickup stick that lifts selected warp threads to create regular eyelets across the cloth. The four-pick sequence repeats throughout, making this a very manageable first pickup-stick project.",
  "type": "PATTERN",
  "categorySlug": "fibre-arts",
  "subCategorySlug": "weaving",
  "difficulty": "INTERMEDIATE",
  "season": null,
  "sourceType": "PUBLIC_DOMAIN",
  "sourceNotes": "- Rigid heddle lace pickup technique is a standard method documented in numerous public domain and contemporary weaving guides. No specific source quotation used.",
